                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the Ms. is written: fol. 198v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a human with a spear, Legend: Gäbrä Giyorgis: fol. 198v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a cross: fol. 197v.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken up: fols. 21r, 86v.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken down: fol. 10v.&#xD;
- Omitted letters, words and passages are inserted interlineally or written in the margin on many fols.: e.g., fols. 4v, 5r, 11r, 29r, 37r, 56r, 73v, 109v.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures on several fols.: e.g., fols. 36r, 42v, 72v, 87r, 99r, 106r, 134r.&#xD;
- Erasures: fols. 95v, 145r, 195v.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 38va-40ra, 64va-65vb, 71rb-72ra.&#xD;
- Pen trials, scribbles and doodles: fols. 86r, 116r, 178v, 197v, 198r.</item>
